-- LME Appoints Nyrstar and Volcan to Lead and Zinc Committee
-- B y   A g n i e s z k a   T r o s z k i e w i c z
-- 2013-05-02T16:07:45Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-02/lme-appoints-nyrstar-and-volcan-to-lead-and-zinc-committee-1-.html
The London Metal Exchange, the world’s
biggest metals marketplace, appointed Paolo Cabrejos of Volcan
Cia. Minera and  Nyrstar (NYR)  Sales & Marketing AG’s Mike Giunti to
its lead and zinc committee, according to the LME website.  Lima-based Volcan is  Peru ’s largest zinc producer.
Brussels-based Nyrstar is the world’s second-largest refined
zinc producer. The LME also appointed Steve Ball of Ocean
Partners USA Inc. and Marek Drosik of Huta Cynku “Miasteczko
Slaskie” SA to the committee. The next meeting is on May 23,
according to the  website .  The LME committees comprise producers, consumers and
traders of various metals. The lead and zinc committee includes
Transamine Trading SA,  Johnson Controls Inc. (JCI)  and Asturiana de
Zinc SA, part of Xstrata.  To contact the reporter on this story:
